---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <!-- src/components/TokiFlowContent.astro -->
  <main class="flow-page">
    <!-- HERO -->
    <section class="flow-hero">
      <div class="flow-hero-inner">
        <div class="flow-hero-card">
          <div class="flow-hero-logo"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- INTRO -->
    <section class="flow-intro">
      <div class="flow-intro-inner">
        <h1 class="flow-title">TÓKI FLOW.</h1>

        <p>
          A flow where insights turn into ideas – and ideas turn into solutions
          that create real value for both brand, customer and planet.
        </p>

        <p>
          Our approach is based on five paths that together form the core of
          TÓKI Flow. They describe not just a process, but a journey – where we
          together move from understanding to change.
        </p>

        <p>
          Each path can stand alone, or we can move through the entire journey
          as one unified partnership. For us, it is not about delivering a task
          – but about creating movement, clarity and results that can be felt.
        </p>

        <div class="flow-first-step">
          <h2>First Step</h2>
          <h3>Purpose</h3>
          <p>
            To create a common foundation — where we understand your packaging’s
            journey and how it can create more value for both business, brand
            and planet.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- STEPS 1 & 2 -->
    <section class="flow-steps flow-steps--12">
      <article class="flow-step-card">
        <div class="flow-step-visual"></div>
        <div class="flow-step-content">
          <span class="flow-step-number">1.</span>
          <p>
            We start by understanding your reality. Mapping the current setup.
            We start with what you already know. We collect existing data and
            your experience — and add our perspective on what works and where
            potential lies.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="flow-step-card flow-step-card--reverse">
        <div class="flow-step-visual"></div>
        <div class="flow-step-content">
          <span class="flow-step-number">2.</span>
          <p>
            Analysis of the packaging journey. We follow the packaging all the
            way — from factory to consumer. We see how form, materials and
            communication interact and where improvements can create value.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>
    </section>

    <!-- STEP 3 + INFO BOXES -->
    <section class="flow-steps flow-steps--3">
      <article class="flow-step-card">
        <div class="flow-step-visual"></div>
        <div class="flow-step-content">
          <span class="flow-step-number">3.</span>
          <p>
            Common direction. We define process, milestones and decision points.
            This is where the common picture of how we work together emerges —
            with clarity and flexibility.
          </p>
        </div>
      </article>

      <div class="flow-extra-text">
        <div>
          <h3>TÓKI Perspective</h3>
          <p>
            We don't just collect insight — we connect it. Seeing the whole
            behind a packaging setup creates clarity that lifts both business
            and narrative.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h3>Typical investment</h3>
          <p>
            This phase is usually around DKK 25–30,000 depending on scope. What
            matters most is starting right — with insight and direction.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA SECTION -->
    <section class="flow-cta">
      <div class="flow-cta-inner">
        <div class="flow-cta-text">
          <h2>Want to shape the future of packaging with us?</h2>
          <p>One of five phases, where we create value – together.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="#contact" class="flow-cta-button">GET IN TOUCH</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
